<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="114" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[813,1456,567,978]" box="[813,913,567,593]" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[813,1456,567,978]" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">
In 1972 Guinot wrote a new label “presumed 
<typeStatus box="[1315,1407,600,626]" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">syntypes</typeStatus>
” for the samples MNHN-IU-2000-4024 (= MNHN-B4024) and MNHN-IU-2000-3546 (= MNHN-B3546) collected by Verreaux in 
<collectingCountry box="[904,1003,695,721]" name="Australia" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Australia</collectingCountry>
. Based on this information, 
<bibRefCitation author="GRIFFIN D. J. G." pageId="25" pageNumber="114" pagination="415 - 440" refId="ref29534" refString="GRIFFIN D. J. G. 1973. - A revision of the two southern temperate shore crabs Leptograpsus variegatus (Fabricius) and Plagusia chabrus (Linnaeus) (Crustacea, Decapoda, Grapsidae). Journal of the Royal Society of New Zealand 3 (3): 415 - 440. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 03036758.1973.10421866" type="journal article" year="1973">Griffin (1973: 418</bibRefCitation>
, 423) mentioned that two 
<typeStatus box="[1138,1229,728,754]" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">syntypes</typeStatus>
were deposited at the MNHN when he recognised the species as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1793" box="[839,1074,792,817]" class="Malacostraca" family="Grapsidae" genus="Leptograpsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variegatus">
<emphasis box="[839,1074,792,817]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Leptograpsus variegatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The larger male from the type series is selected here as 
<typeStatus box="[1014,1116,823,849]" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The entry date in the CAA of a considerable material of the Verreaux collection from 
<collectingRegion country="Australia" name="Tasmania" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Tasmania</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[893,988,887,913]" name="Australia" pageId="25" pageNumber="114">Australia</collectingCountry>
is 1847, which corroborates the hypothesis that H. Milne Edwards has established his new species after this Verreaux material (see Appendix).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
